President Biden spoke with Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas to emphasize the U.S.'s commitment to strengthening the U.S.-Palestinian partnership. They discussed the tensions in Jerusalem and the West Bank and expressed their shared desire for peaceful coexistence in Jerusalem for people of all backgrounds. President Biden updated President Abbas on U.S. diplomatic engagement regarding the conflict and stressed the need for Hamas to stop firing rockets into Israel. They expressed concern for the loss of innocent lives, including children, in the ongoing violence. President Biden expressed support for enabling the Palestinian people to enjoy dignity, security, freedom, and economic opportunities, highlighting the recent U.S. decision to resume assistance to Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza. He also reiterated his commitment to a negotiated two-state solution as the best way to resolve the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.